This paper is most likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on the generative perspective of the discriminative CNN in generating object and texture patterns in natural scenes. It also uses pre-learned filters from the CNN at the convolutional layers, which is a common technique in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically in learning the generative FRAME model using the CNN filters, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Additionally, the paper mentions the use of binary latent variables in the learning algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper proposes a new layer of CNN units using a generative CNN model, which may also make it relevant to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
